description: This full-color special collects rare Little Gloomy stories from Disney Adventures Magazine in comic book form for the very first time! In "The Witch's Cauldron," an old friend with evil intentions pays Gloomy a visit, can Gloomy combat the relentless evil of dozens of tiny, purple cats? Then in "The Curse of the Mummies," Mummy falls dangerously ill, and the one thing that can save him is a rare tea, grown only in the forbidden city of Mummyville! What vile fate awaits those who trespass into this mysterious land? Featuring an introduction by Disney Adventures Magazine editor Steve Behling.
name: Little Gloomy Adventures

description:
This is the trade paperback format that collects regular issues 1-4 from Moonstone's regular The Phantom series.

The modern day Phantom continues his quest for law and order in the jungles of Bangalla and beyond in this collection of first four issues of The Phantom series.

First, things get personal in "Stones of Blood", as The Phantom breaks up a slave camp in Bangalla where captives are mining a vast diamond field. Then in "Curse of the Phantom", a great evil has haunted the Walker family deep into the woods of Bangalla!
name: Death in the Deep Woods

description:
This is the trade paperback format that collects regular issues 5-11 from Moonstone's regular The Phantom series.

The stories covered and issue numbers breakdown are as follows:

5&6 - "Damnation Game"

7&8 - "The Aviatrix"

9&10 - "Slave Trade"

11 - "Nanamaru"

Included here are the amazing adventures of Blood diamonds, Slavery, Zombies, angry female Aviatrix, and the ever present sinister Singh Brotherhood!

The Phantom comes to the urban jungle in America, has a run in with the FBI, is out-gunned on a speeding train and comes face-to-face with a secret from his past!
name: Jungle Action

description:
This is the trade paperback format that collects regular issues 12-20 & 26 from Moonstone's regular The Phantom series.

Invisible Children is a charitable organization that helps educate and save African children who are pressed into military service. The movement has received national media attention from TV shows, to celebrities, to press!
name: The Man Who Cannot Die

This is the trade paperback format that collects regular issues 21-25 from Moonstone's regular The Phantom series.

Rebels warring in Bangallan jungles, terrorist attacks in the streets of Mawitaan and an old enemy suddenly freed from prison for no logical reason. This story collection describes if these are part of something or part of something far more sinister.

description:
This monster tome volume of one shot novellas. It collects all 13 issues of Moonstone's series The Phantom Generations.

A montser-tome collection of 325 pages black and white art telling a tale of each one of the 21 Phantoms! For some reason this book is black and white while all the 13 individual issues were published in full color.

Included as a BONUS in this TPB are two unpublished stories from Josh Aitken, Mike Bullock and Tony Isabella.
name: The Phantom: Generations

description: The Hulk joins the circus! But why? And only Captain America can save Dr. Strange, the Sorcerer Supreme! But how? Circus smashing and demon demolishing abound in these two super stories!
name: The Big Idea!

description: Time Lincoln's Traveler's Team faces their greatest challenge yet when they prepare to fight Void Stalin and his Chrono-Communists at their base the Void itself! But by the time they arrive, Stalin's forces have apparently been driven off by a powerful newcomer, a literal one-man army! The travelers are are soon overwhelmed. Their only hope is new mysterious ally, a man known only as...J-FTL-K.

volume.name: Time Lincoln: Jack To The Future

name: A Training Guide On Homosexual Conduct Police

description:
Since 1936, he has been thrilling his newspaper audience worldwide. Now, welcome the comics return of the first costumed

adventure hero, The Phantom! Successful weapons-dealer, Solomon Bishop, has a problem: The Ghost Who Walks! The Phantom is the only thing stopping a multimillion dollar sale of rifles equipped with "re-positioning" technology. So what's a rich and evil businessman to do? Why, hire an exotic raven-haired killing machine to do your dirty work for you, of course!

Phantom, please be careful — this woman's an "assassin's assassin," and she hasn't missed her mark yet
name: The Phantom: Ghost Killer

volume.name: The Phantom: The Ghost Who Walks
